results.name: Decimal expansion of 4th Du Bois Reymond constant.
reference: S. R. Finch, Mathematical Constants, Cambridge, 2003, pp. 237-239.
link: Eric W. Weisstein, MathWorld: Du Bois Reymond Constants.
formula: 2 sum(k = 1..infinity) (1 + (x_k)^2)^(-2) = (e^4 - 4e^2 - 25)/8, where x_k is the k-th root of t = tan t and e is the natural logarithm base (approx. 2.71828).
results.author: _Alonso del Arte_, Feb 24 2012
